de.unisiegen.tpml.core.util
Class IterableNodeList

java.lang.Object
  de.unisiegen.tpml.core.util.IterableNodeList
All Implemented Interfaces:
Iterable<Node>, NodeList
public final class IterableNodeList
extends Object
implements Iterable<Node>, NodeList

This is a decorator class for the NodeList class, which represents a list of Nodes below a parent node in a DOM Document. Using this class one can easily iterate over the list of child nodes below a given document node. For example the following code fragment 

 NodeList childNodes = parent.getChildNodes();
 for (int i = 0; i < childNodes; ++i) {
   Node node = childNodes.item(i);
   // process the node...
 }
can be transform into 
 for (Node node : new IterableNodeList (parent)) {
   // process the node...
 }
which is not only shorter, but also easier to understand.
